  "text_preview": "\"stove\" American Sign Language (ASL) ASL Lessons | Bookstore | Library | ASL University Main ► STOVE : The American Sign Language (ASL) sign for \"stove\" STOVE: I recommend you just spell out the letters: S-T-O-V-E. Sample sentence: MY PARENTS KEEP MATCHES WHERE? STOVE NEXT-TO DRAWER INDEX-there. But since sometimes you might see someone doing the actual sign for stove so I'm going to show it here. To express the concept of \"stove,\" sign \"cook\" then \"flat + sides\" to show the top and sides of the stove. STOVE-(descriptive_version) (not recommended) Also see: animation Use a double motion to turn the verb \"BAKE\" into the noun \"OVEN.\" OVEN or \"baking\" The verb \"bake\" uses a single motion representing the placing of food in an oven. BAKE: Notes: Also see: COOK Also see: BAKE * Want to help sup"
}
